1. Open Sublime
2. Ctrl+Shift+P, select Install Package Control.
3. Once again, Ctrl+Shift+P and now we select Install Package. Search and install Sync Settings.
4. Ctrl+Shift+P and select Sync Settings: Download.

This will ask us for the gist_id:

{
  "gist_id": "4f386eadf81a6cc236ed309bec41ecac"
}


If you have errors during syncing, please try adding this User Settings:
1. Go to preferences, open Settings, and on the right pane, paste this json:

{
  "detect_indentation": false,
  "folder_exclude_patterns":
  [
    ".git",
    "node_modules",
    "public"
  ],
  "font_face": "Source Code Pro",
  "font_size": 11,
  "highlight_modified_tabs": true,
  "hot_exit": false,
  "ignored_packages":
  [
    "Rust",
    "Vintage"
  ],
  "rulers":
  [
    100
  ],
  "tab_size": 2,
  "theme_primer_sidebar_font_large": true,
  "theme_primer_sidebar_tree_small": true,
  "translate_tabs_to_spaces": true,
  "trim_trailing_white_space_on_save": true
}




You will be able to download the common config for developers.
